âœ… 2. Dependency Caching (Maven)
ğŸ”´ Problem

Maven downloads dependencies on every build

ğŸŸ¢ Solution
environment {
    MAVEN_OPTS = "-Dmaven.repo.local=${WORKSPACE}/.m2"
}

//Docker Agent (Even Better)
agent {
    docker {
        image 'maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17'
        args '-v $HOME/.m2:/root/.m2'
    }
}

â± Time Saved
Dependency resolution: 10â€“12 min â†’ <1 min

âœ… 3. Incremental Builds
ğŸ”´ Problem
mvn clean package
//Forces full rebuild
ğŸŸ¢ Solution
mvn compile
//or
mvn -DskipTests install
//Multi-threaded Maven
mvn -T 1C compile
â± Time Saved
Build: 15 min â†’ 6â€“8 min

âœ… 4. Docker Layer Caching (CRITICAL)
ğŸ”´ Bad Dockerfile
COPY . .
RUN mvn clean package
ğŸŸ¢ Optimized Dockerfile (BEST PRACTICE)
# ---- Build Stage ----
FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build
WORKDIR /app

COPY pom.xml .
RUN mvn dependency:go-offline

COPY src ./src
RUN mvn package -DskipTests

# ---- Runtime Stage ----
FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre
WORKDIR /app

COPY --from=build /app/target/app.jar app.jar
ENTRYPOINT ["java","-jar","app.jar"]
//Enable BuildKit
environment {
    DOCKER_BUILDKIT = "1"
}

â± Time Saved
Docker build: 8 min â†’ 2â€“3 min

â€œI reduced pipeline time by parallelizing tests, caching dependencies, enabling incremental Maven builds, and optimizing Docker layer caching using multi-stage builds and BuildKit. This cut build time by over 50% while keeping reliability.â€
